You need to write a program that determines whether a given year is a leap year using a single, complex if statement.

The mathematical rules for determining a leap year are as follows:

It must be divisible by 4.

However, if it is also divisible by 100, it is not a leap year...

...Unless it is also divisible by 400, in which case it is a leap year.

Your task is to take an integer year as input and use these rules to evaluate it.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Input Format

A single line containing an integer, year.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Constraints

1 <= year <= 100,000

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Output Format

Print a single string in the following format:

If the year is a leap year, print: [year] is a leap year

If the year is not a leap year, print: [year] is not a leap year
